message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Saudi Arabia in the past 100 years is the discovery of oil in commercial quantities. This discovery occurred in 1938, when oil was found in the eastern region of the country. The subsequent development of the oil industry transformed Saudi Arabia from a predominantly agrarian society into one of the world's leading oil producers and exporters. The revenue generated from oil exports has had a profound impact on the country's economy, infrastructure, and social development. It has also played a crucial role in shaping Saudi Arabia's geopolitical influence on the global stage.
